I dislike the #ifdef config <br />option thing (either it works or it doesn't).<br /><br />It also does it the right way: using LOCK_PREFIX means that you catch <br />exactly the users that depend on SMP, and not _all_ "lock" prefixes (as <br />mentioned, some of the lock prefixes are there as memory fences and are <br />valid and needed even on UP). So me likee.<br /><br />The only question being whether you'd actually want to nop out the <br />spinlock instructions _entirely_ (in addition to changing the nops on <br />things like semaphores). Without the lock, they're not that expensive, but <br />hey, it's still a useless (memory-modifying) instruction.<br /><br />		Linus<br />-<br />To unsubscribe from this list: send the line "unsubscribe linux-kernel" in<br />the body of a message to majordomo&#64;vger.kernel.org<br />More majordomo info at  <a href="http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html">http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html</a><br />Please read the FAQ at  <a href="http://www.tux.org/lkml/">http://www.tux.org/lkml/</a><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
